Regional Regulatory Affairs Manager
Regional Regulatory Affairs Manager (RE-12509633) Singapore
Responsibilities
Develop and implement regulatory strategy across the region, by successfully communicating between local affiliates and the regional team.
Manages regulatory compliance throughout the life cycle of products.
Liaise closely with health authorities and foster good working relationship.
Lead and manage team members, by motivating and guiding in a most efficient manners.
Requirements
Bachelor’s degree, background in Business or Science will be preferred
Strong regulatory background, at least 5 year experience
Regulatory experience in a pharmaceutical company, preferably with regional regulatory experience
Registered pharmacist an advantage
Strong communication skill with competitive mindset
